  "title": "The BMI-HDEEG dataset 1",
  "description": "A high-density scalp electroencephalogram (HD-EEG) dataset acquired during sensorimotor rhythm-based brain-computer interface (BCI) tasks. The dataset comprises recordings from multiple subjects performing motor imagery and related sensorimotor activities, designed to support the development and validation of BCI systems. This resource provides a comprehensive foundation for investigating neural correlates of motor planning and brain-computer communication.",
